    "response": "To compute the **sample standard deviation** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{25, 10, 0, 9, -1, -14, -21\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the mean (average) of the data set\n\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 + (-1) + (-14) + (-21)}{7}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 - 1 - 14 - 21}{7}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{25 + 10 + 9 - 1 - 14 - 21}{7} = \\frac{20}{7} \\approx 2.857\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Subtract the mean from each data point and square the result\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(25 - 2.857)^2 &= 22.143^2 \\approx 491.06 \\\\\n(10 - 2.857)^2 &= 7.143^2 \\approx 51.03 \\\\\n(0 - 2.857)^2 &= (-2.857)^2 \\approx 8.162 \\\\\n(9 - 2.857)^2 &= 6.143^2 \\approx 37.72 \\\\\n(-1 - 2.857)^2 &= (-3.857)^2 \\approx 14.87 \\\\\n(-14 - 2.857)^2 &= (-16.857)^2 \\approx 284.01 \\\\\n(-21 - 2.857)^2 &= (-23.857)^2 \\approx 568.78 \\\\\n\\end{align*}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared differences\n\n$$\n\\text{Sum of squares} = 491.06 + 51.03 + 8.162 + 37.72 + 14.87 + 284.01 + 568.78\n$$\n\n$$\n\\approx"
